<p>
<p>Suppose we do a probability experiment with a mass production of light bulbs. We take a sample size of 120. Define two chance variables: X is the number of bulbs that are defective, and Y is the burn time per bulb. Which random variable in this probability experiment is a discrete variable?</p>
</p>]]></text>
</questiontext>
<generalfeedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
</p>]]></text>
</generalfeedback>
<penalty>0</penalty>
<defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
<shuffleanswers>false</shuffleanswers>
<single>true</single>
<answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
<answer fraction="100" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X is a discrete variable.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X is a discrete variable..: Correct
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Y is a discrete variable.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
Y is a discrete variable :: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X and Y are both discrete variables.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X and Y are both discrete variables…: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
</answer>
<answer fraction="0" format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X and Y are both not discrete variables.
</p>]]></text>
<feedback format="html">
<text><![CDATA[<p>
X and Y are both not discrete variables…: Incorrect
</p>]]></text>
</feedback>
